Input - (session id, project_id, compressed file)

This parses the compressed code file and creates a concrete syntax tree using library like tree-sitter
Then it navigates through each component and forms a new decompressed file.

1. If it just landed onto the definition of a component, then reach out to relaxCommentOut in the decompressor module
Pass in all the required details mentioned in the relaxCommentOut and get the comment block to be appended right before
this component in the new decompressed file.

2. If it is a class/method/package/any component, apply the relaxcompactBlock strategy in the compressor module
Pass in all the required details mentioned in the relaxCompactBlock and get the corresponding identifier to be used
for the component to be replaced inline. If the response is null, just move on with the navigation and add that component as is
to the new decompressed file.

Ouput - (session_id, project_id, decompressed file)